). Stramineous, with black punctuations irregularly distributed. Head, with punctures forming a «C» laterad of each eye; punctures on the base of head and along the juga; margins of juga outlined by black. Pronotum densely punctured; punctures forming transverse lines on the posterior two thirds; cicatrices lined by punctures. Scutellum uniformly covered by punctures, except for the basal disc, black. Corium uniformly covered by punctures, except for a central callus. Connexivum finely outlined by black. Legs weakly punctured; margins of tibia outlined by black. Ventral abdominal surface densely punctured, completely dark in males and slightly stramineous toward the center, in females.

